[{"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion Saarbr\u00fccken S-2354 - 14 - St 222S-2354St 422 - S-2354 - 1 / 97S-2354 -S-2354 | Bibliography of the relevant administrative instructions: BerlinOFD Berlin St 422 - S-2354 - 1/97 from 07/05 / 97 EStK \u00a7 9 EStG Fach 9 Nr 1002 / I OFD Berlin St 422 - S-2354 - 1/97 from 17/07/97 EStK \u00a7 9 EStG Fach 9 Nr 1002 / IIIEStG: 9EStG: 7 / 1EStG: 7/1 / 5EStG: 9/1 / 1EStG: 9/1/3 / 7EStG: 12 / 1EStG: 19OFD Berlin St 422 - S-2354 - 1/97 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "6 6 1997 EStK \u00a7 9 EStG Fach 9 Nr 1002 / IIBartone Inf 2000 747Bartone Inf 2000 747 Expenses for computers, peripheral devices and software as income-related expenses Orders of 24 1 1986 30 8 1988 and 8 11 1988 Az"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "I General: II Distinguishing features: A"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Hardware1 Portable computers (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Laptops, notebooks, palmtops) 2 Non-mobile devices21 Location of the computer22 Amount of acquisition costs23 Central processing unit24 Capacity of the main memory (RAM) 25 drives26 Monitor27 Printer3 Compatibility with the employer's computers4 Multimedia equipment5 Online servicesB"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "software"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Other demarcation featuresIII Tax assessmentIV Service life of computers and softwareV Computer questionnaire In the above purchase orders, regulations have been made on the tax deductibility of expenses for computers as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The increasing spread of computers, the changes in the market and the previous case law have now made it necessary to revise the purchase orders and adapt them to today's conditions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The purchase orders are hereby canceled and replaced by the following instructions: I General: Expenses for the acquisition of computers and peripheral devices generally represent costs for mixed-use assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs cannot regularly be divided into a professional and a private part in a simple and easily verifiable manner according to objective standards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The costs can therefore only be taken into account for tax purposes if the employee can prove or credible that he uses the equipment almost exclusively for professional purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, the tax claims must be derived from external, objectively ascertainable circumstances, because the extent of the actual private and professional use of a computer and peripheral devices cannot be ascertained either directly, promptly or simply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In order to avoid an unacceptable intrusion into the privacy of the employee, the criteria of an almost exclusive professional use must be typified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "II Delimitation features: Conclusions on professional and private use can be drawn primarily from the technical features of the computer system acquired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the technical equipment, features have been compiled below that can serve to distinguish between private and professional spheres"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, these are only indications that are to be assessed on a case-by-case basis: A."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Hardware1 Portable computers (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Laptops, notebooks, palmtops) Portable computers contain at least the central processing unit (CPU), the keyboard, one or more storage drives and a display (screen) in one housing."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, other equipment features, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "a (PCMCIA) modem, a CD-ROM drive, a sound card or a multimedia-compatible processor (CPU with so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "MMX technology)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Since these computers are, however, due to their design - with the same performance - significantly more expensive than non-mobile devices, it can generally be assumed that these additional costs will only be borne if they are required by the job"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer conclusively demonstrates the (almost) exclusive professional use of the portable computer, there are therefore no concerns about recognizing the acquisition costs as income-related costs over its useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "2 Non-mobile devices21 Location of the computer If the computer is at the taxpayer's workplace with his employer, the nature of the work equipment must regularly be affirmed; because the employer will hardly tolerate private use of the computer during working hours and private use will hardly occur outside of working hours"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Another point of reference for the character of the work equipment of the computer can be its location in the home office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, if the taxpayer does not have a study, the reverse does not follow from this, however, that the computer in the taxpayer's apartment lacks the professional reason"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "22 Amount of acquisition costs The amount of acquisition costs for computers and peripheral devices is not a suitable criterion for delimiting the actual use of these devices in view of the considerable price decline in this market that has continued for years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "23 Central processing unit The performance of a computer, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "the speed with which data is processed and output is primarily determined by the central processing unit (CPU) used in it and the clock frequency of the same, specified in megahertz (MHz)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In the area of \u200b\u200bpersonal computers (PC), the CPU type designations of the market-leading manufacturer INTEL have resulted in the following performance classes: 286 Use for simpler data processing (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Word processing under the DOS operating system)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "No longer available in stores *! Current software i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "no longer executable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "386 Application for simple data processing (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Word processing, spreadsheet, databases under MS-WINDOWS)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "No longer in stores *! Current software i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "no longer useful"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "486 CPU with clock frequencies between 25 and 133 MHz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Use in more complex data processing (word processing, spreadsheet, databases, (conditional) image processing, program development)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Suitable for the use of operating systems with a graphical user interface (in particular Microsoft WINDOWS 31)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Pentium / MMXCurrent \"standard CPU\" for newly purchased computers - clock frequency up to over 200 MHz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Significantly more powerful than its predecessor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Equipped with \"MMX\" technology since 1997"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The addition MMX denotes the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "\"Multimedia Extension\", i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The instruction set of the conventional Pentium CPU has been expanded and thus enables faster processing, especially of multimedia applications programmed specifically for MMX technology (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Presentations, graphics, videos, games)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Operating system suitable especially for Microsoft Windows 95 but also for Windows NT or IBM OS / 2 Pentium Pro / Pentium II Most powerful CPU from the manufacturer INTEL - clock frequency up to 300 MHz; Particularly suitable for the use of real 32-bit operating systems (Windows NT, IBM OS / 2) and corresponding (expensive) 32-bit software"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The price of the personal computer equipped with it is also determined largely as a function of the performance of the CPU, although it should be noted that more and more non-name or discount providers are also offering high-performance computers at low cost"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the computers referred to as personal computers (PC), there are manufacturers of other computer systems which, however, are not readily compatible with the PC standard"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "First and foremost here is the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "To name Apple computers that use their computers with CPUs from"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "\"Motorola\" manufactures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The command set of these central units is fundamentally incompatible with that of conventional PCs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, the limits of system compatibility are now fluid here too"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "With the \"Power PC\" model series from"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "On request, Apple will use the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "\"Soft-Windows\" is supplied, a computer software that enables the use of Windows applications written for an IBM-compatible PC on these APPLE computers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, an additional plug-in card has been announced, which - equipped with a Pentium processor - should ensure full system compatibility with \"conventional\" PCs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "24 Capacity of the main memory (RAM) Just like the CPU used, the size of the main memory in the computer also plays an important role in its performance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The larger the RAM, the more data the computer can process - without time-consuming intermediate storage on the hard drive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "A low storage capacity of up to four megabytes (MB) in the main memory of a computer casts doubt on the purpose of the job"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The use of job-specific software, in particular using an operating system with a graphical user interface (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Windows 95 OS / 2 u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "), regularly requires a larger storage capacity (min"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "8 MG, better 16/32 MB)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "25 Drives Nowadays, permanent storage of computer data takes place regularly on 35-inch floppy or hard disk drives"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Their use therefore does not allow any tax-relevant conclusions to be drawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Only a high storage capacity of the hard disk from around 5 gigabytes (GB) speaks in favor of a professional reason for the expenditure, if only because of the higher acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In order to secure larger amounts of data, so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Streamer (= special magnetic tape storage devices) or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "other drive technologies (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "ZIP-Drive, a: Drive, magneto-optical drives) with high storage capacity are used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Since backing up data i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "only makes sense if the data is not used in another way, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "can be easily restored by reinstalling the existing software, the presence of such a drive is an indication of professional use of the computer if these peripheral devices are used to store the professional data"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to the aforementioned drives, a so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "CD-ROM drive only reads data from a finished data CD"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If the computer is equipped with the appropriate hardware and / or software (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Sound card, MPEG card or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Software MPEG etc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ") the CD-ROM drive is also suitable for all applications for which a CD is used in the entertainment electronics sector, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "CD player, photo CD playback, video CD"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The CD-ROM drive is therefore often a prerequisite for so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Multimedia applications, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Applications that aim at the simultaneous processing of sound, images and data"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The private use of a suitably equipped computer is also conceivable in the field of multimedia applications (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Play special video CDs, interactive games and learning programs, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "), but without concrete evidence it cannot be assumed that the taxpayer uses the computer accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The presence of a CD-ROM drive is therefore not in itself suitable for assuming private shared use that is detrimental to recognition as advertising expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "26 Monitor Only special computer monitors can be connected to computers for displaying the data on a screen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "These monitors are connected to the computer via a separate interface"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Due to the significant drop in prices that has occurred in this area and the ever increasing distribution of so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "graphical user interfaces, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Windows, OS / 2 etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ", the use of color monitors has meanwhile become standard, a computer use that speaks against the professional cause cannot be inferred from this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, if the purchased computer monitor is a high-quality device (from around 2000 DM), the comparatively high purchase price is an indication of the professional reason for the expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "27 Printers Also in the area of \u200b\u200bprinters, acquisition costs are not a suitable criterion for differentiating professional use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "So are z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Inkjet printers with high quality printouts are available on the market today for less than 500 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The mere purchase of a higher-priced printer using laser technology can be an indication of professional use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The lack of a printer, on the other hand, still speaks against practically exclusive professional use of the entire computer system"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Nevertheless, the lack of a printer when purchasing a new computer system is not harmful from the outset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Rather, the taxpayer is given a \"consideration period\" for the subsequent purchase of a printer of around six months"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, if the printer is absent for a longer period of time, the employee must demonstrate that it makes sense to do without printouts of the results (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "because these are carried out by his employer)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "3 Compatibility with the employer's computers Decisive for the professional purpose of the computer system purchased by the taxpayer is the question of whether the results obtained in domestic work are used professionally - and not technically - in his employer's business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The compatibility between the computer system of the employee and that of the employer is not decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "4 Multimedia equipment The term \"multimedia\" has been defining the computer world since 1996"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Multimedia applications are always suitable for use in the area of \u200b\u200bprivate life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "They are increasingly also supported by the hardware; the first graphics cards with so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "3-D acceleration for the \"normal user\" available on the market"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "According to various test reports in relevant trade journals, the new hardware also offers a speed advantage, in some cases significant, over conventional hardware, without being significantly more expensive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition of a powerful computer system can therefore hardly do without the (partial) equipment with the most modern multimedia components"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, PCs with \"outdated\" technology can no longer be bought a short time after new technologies have been introduced to the market"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "At the same time, multimedia applications also make the private use of a computer more interesting"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Computer games and simulations that run in real-time 3D graphics have a higher entertainment value than previous 2D applications, which is why it is not uncommon for hardware that supports multimedia to be supplied with software that is intended to make the hardware's multimedia capabilities clear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "With modern 3-D graphics cards, game software is therefore often included that can certainly not be used for professional purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Nevertheless, this alone must not be used to infer a private use of the computer that is not subordinate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Rather, there must be additional circumstances that make an (almost) exclusive professional use unlikely"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the PC is equipped with a special 3-D or video graphics accelerator card in addition to its previous graphics card, the (rebuttable) presumption speaks in favor of a private reason for the equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "5 Online services Insofar as the taxpayer is a user of an online service, harmful private use of the computer can be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The currently best known online services are: American Online (AOL) CompuserveMicrosoft Network (msn) T-Online"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "These online services allow the user to use the Internet in addition to the provider-specific online service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, there are numerous providers who are known as so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Providers enable Internet access even without a special online service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "These include"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "EuNetGermanyNetMetroNetsnafu u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The range of programs offered by online services and the Internet is so extensive that, although it can be beneficial to the profession, (almost) exclusive use of the services is generally excluded due to the existing prohibition of division and deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "A different view can only apply to taxpayers who obtain their professional data and information from a company's intranet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to the Internet, the intranet is a company's own data network, in which i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "data from any other provider cannot be accessed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Software If a taxpayer only uses job-specific software, the professional use of the hardware can also be inferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The use of software, on the other hand, which can also be used privately (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Word processing programs) does not allow any conclusions to be drawn from a tax point of view"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, indications for private or professional use of such ambivalent software can be derived from the acquisition costs and the technical possibilities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The more expensive the software and the more extensive its possible uses, the more the assumption speaks in favor of professional use of this software"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, the relationship between the number and acquisition costs of both types of software (job-specific and ambivalent software) must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "- Are only the operating systems (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Windows 95 OS / 2 etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ") stated as software, this does not indicate (almost) exclusive professional use of the computer, as this software mainly serves to provide the basis for the use of the actual (professional or private) user software, such as word processing, spreadsheets, programming languages, games, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ", to build"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If an employee has children in education, private shared use of the computer system can be rebutted if there is no other computer system in the taxpayer's household"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "However, this assumption in itself is usually not sufficient to deny the deduction of the expenses claimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If the tax office cannot make actual determinations about the extent of use by the children, additional circumstances must be added that speak for a not inconsiderable private use of the computer system (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "the presence of a joystick or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Joypads)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Another indication of the professional reason for purchasing the computer system is, however, its subsidy from the taxpayer's employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "After assessing all the criteria relevant to the decision, it can be assumed that the computer and peripheral devices are not used for private purposes if their share of the total use does not exceed 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the advertising costs character of the expenses for the acquisition of the equipment must be affirmed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, due to \u00a7 12 No. 1 EStG, a proportional consideration only in the amount of the professional usage share is not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to any software used by the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "III Tax assessment If, according to this, a deduction as advertising expenses is considered, the following must be observed: The central unit and the peripheral devices (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Printer, screen, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ") can be assessed independently, but not independently usable assets, because according to their professional purpose they can only be used together, are technically coordinated with one another and also inserted into the professional context of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Your acquisition or production costs are therefore not immediately deductible as advertising expenses, even if they do not amount to more than DM 800 excluding sales tax, but can only be deducted over the useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Portable computers (laptops, notebooks, palmtops), in which the manufacturer has brought together the central unit (data processing), the keyboard (data input), the storage drives (data backup) and the display (data output) in a compact housing, can always be used independently , with the result that their acquisition costs - if they are up to DM 800 excluding sales tax - can be deducted immediately as income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, there is also the option of deducting the acquisition costs over the useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If a computer that is already in use at work is e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "retrofitted by installing a larger hard disk or expanding the RAM memory, the residual value at the time of installation increases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Example: Purchase cost of the computer Jan"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "19,935,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Depreciation (1993 - 1995) 3000 DM, residual value 2000 DM + installation of a larger hard drive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "19961000 DMAfA assessment amount (new) 3000 DM Remaining useful life 2 years = depreciation (1996 - 1997) 1500 DM each An extension of the remaining useful life is only possible if essential components of the computer (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "the CPU) must be replaced and an actual extension of the expected service life can be assumed as a result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns if the information provided by the taxpayer is complied with with regard to the remaining useful life after upgrading"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "IV Service life of computers and software With BMF letter of April 18, 1997 - IV A 8 - S-1551 - 37/97 - (BStBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "1997 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "376 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ") the depreciation table for generally applicable assets has been revised"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "According to the current"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "61332 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "61333 of this table is the typical service life for workstations, personal computers, notebooks, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "as well as for peripheral devices basically four - and not as before five - years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "This table applies to all capital goods that were acquired or manufactured after June 30, 1997"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If the expected useful life is less than 4 years, there must be special objective, verifiable reasons, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "increased wear and tear due to frequent transport of the (portable) computer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Simply referring to the rapid new developments in the IT area is not enough"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "When purchasing used computers, a shorter useful life can be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The depreciation period for software is 3 to 5 years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The possibility of immediate business expenses deduction of acquisition costs of up to DM 800 excluding sales tax for independently usable computers (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Laptop, notebook, palmtops) or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "for so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Trivial software (see R 31 a Paragraph 1 EStR) remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, the taxpayer has the option of unusual technical or economic wear and tear in accordance with Section 9 (1) sentence 3 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "To assert \u00a7 7 paragraph 1 sentence 5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "For this it is also necessary to make credible the circumstances that led to the extraordinary technical or economic wear and tear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If a taxpayer claims exceptional economic wear and tear on a computer of the \"486 or a lower performance class\", there are no concerns about following the information provided by the taxpayer without further examination if he explains the reasons for this conclusively and comprehensibly and the total useful life of the computer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "has been at least 3 years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the provisions of Section 44 Paragraph 3 LStR must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "V Computer questionnaire The previously used form (F 175 - 0889) to check the expenses has been revised (see Appendix)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "An estimated edition will be sent to the tax offices shortly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "(The questionnaire attached in the annex was not included in the case of tax claims of a PC)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "--- Annex: Questionnaire for tax claims of a PC Questionnaire for tax claims of a PC According to the provisions of the data protection laws, it is pointed out that the requested data is based on \u00a7\u00a7 149 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "of the tax code and (in the wage tax reduction procedure) of Section 39a (2) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Income tax return 199 Claiming a personal computer (PC) Dear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In your income tax return, you claim expenses for a personal computer (PC) as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "In order to be able to check whether the claimed expenses for the PC can be taken into account for tax purposes, I ask you to refer to the following points or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Questions in detail no later than"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Comment and submit this letter to the tax office again"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "One copy is intended for your records"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If the space provided for answering the questions is not sufficient, please use a separate sheet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "General: 1 Exact designation (type, type and manufacturer) of the hardware (computer and the connected peripherals (monitor, printer, etc.)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ")) Acquisition costs: 2 acquisition costs of the PC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Please enclose the invoices if they have not yet been submitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "DM21 Subsidies received from the employer for the acquisition costs - Yes, in the amount of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "DM- No Technical features and programs: 3 Equipment of the computer 31 Size of the working memory (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "4 8 or 16 MB) 32 CPU manufacturer and type designation For non-Intel processors: CPU performance class comparable to the specification - i 286 / i 386- i 486- Pentium- Pentium Pro / II4 Further equipment / accessories: 41 Modem / ISDN- Card available? - Yes- No42 Joystick / joypad available? - Yes- No43 Other equipment / accessories5 Are you a member of an online service (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "T-Online, AOL, Compuserve, msn) or have you received from other providers (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "eunet, metronet, germanyNet, snafu) Internet access? - Yes - No6 Do you also use other online connections (mailboxes, company intranet (please enclose confirmation from your employer) and the like"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": ")? - Yes, namely- No 7 Which operating system and which user programs are installed on your computer? For the user programs, please indicate whether they are commercially available programs, programs from the employer or programs you have created yourself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Information on professional use8 How is the claimed PC used by you in detail for your job and at what location (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "at the workplace at the employer, in the home office) is it installed? 9 Are the work results used or processed in your workplace? - Yes (please enclose confirmation from the employer) - No 10 To what extent is the PC used on average for professional purposes (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "1 hour a day, 10 hours a month)? 11 In what form and to what extent is the PC used by you or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "used by other household members beyond the purposes mentioned under point 8? Finally, I would like to note that - if tax recognition takes place - the expenses for the PC are not to be taken into account immediately in one sum if the acquisition costs (excluding sales tax) are 80,000 Exceed DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Rather, the total costs have to be spread over the useful life of the computer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The useful life is generally 5 years if purchased or manufactured before 1 7 1997 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "4 years if purchased or manufactured after June 30, 1997"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "The complete PC system represents a uniform economic asset because the individual parts of the PC and the accessories can only be used as a unit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "If you purchased the PC in the first half of the year, for reasons of simplicity, the full amount of the annual depreciation can be claimed this year, and if you purchased it in the second half of the year, half the annual amount can be claimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Sincerely, I confirm that I have given the information on the above questionnaire truthfully to the best of my knowledge and belief"}, {"meta": {"name": "0138652.xml"}, "text": "Place, date Signature EDV-Recht wage tax income tax / wage tax / church tax income tax / wage tax / church tax SaarlandBerlin"}]